div1.p:
170. 




                     JOHN GERRANS (42) 



                        PLEADED GUILTY
                   to 

                     embezzling and stealing £1 3s. 7d., the moneys of 



                        Robert James White, his master; 



                     also to stealing two crates of ginger-beer, and other articles, the property of his master; 



                     also to forging and uttering an order for the delivery of goods; 


                     and also to unlawfully making a false entry in a document of account.—



                        Eight Months' Hard Labour.
